Fasten your seatbelts newbies!!
Rolling out the first event of Pre Babies' Week Out.

This quote from a teenager girl whose writings have so profoundly affected humanity speaks volumes about the power of a pen and a creative mind. 
Literary and Debating Society bestows upon you the opportunity to wreath your delightful ideas and notions into a sublime story. We invite all the prolific writers out there to ROOST-A-DOODLE DOO. 

Have you hated the fate of your favourite character in your favourite movie or TV series? Have you imagined a climax that could put the director to shame? If yes,send in your articles on *How Would you Re-Structure your Favourite Movie/TV Series*

1.Mail your entries to lds1968nitjsr@gmail.com
2.There is no word limit.
3.The deadline for submission is 31 August.
4.Restrict yourselves to Hindi/English.

Let go of all your inhibitions & let that imaginative story teller inside you come up to the surface. Pick up the pen and jot down all the wondrous thoughts that your mind begets. Go berserk in imagination & let us savour your scrumptious creative juices through your write ups.

Winners will receive exciting prizes.

Fasten your seatbelts newbies!!
Rolling out the first event of Pre Babies' Week Out.

This quote from a teenager girl whose writings have so profoundly affected humanity speaks volumes about the power of a pen and a creative mind. 
Literary and Debating Society bestows upon you the opportunity to wreath your delightful ideas and notions into a sublime story. We invite all the prolific writers out there to ROOST-A-DOODLE DOO. 

Have you hated the fate of your favourite character in your favourite movie or TV series? Have you imagined a climax that could put the director to shame? If yes,send in your articles on *How Would you Re-Structure your Favourite Movie/TV Series*
Adhere to the following rules:
1.Mail your entries to lds1968nitjsr@gmail.com
2.There is no word limit.
3.The deadline for submission is 31 August.
4.Restrict yourselves to Hindi/English.

Let go of all your inhibitions & let that imaginative story teller inside you come up to the surface. Pick up the pen and jot down all the wondrous thoughts that your mind begets. Go berserk in imagination & let us savour your scrumptious creative juices through your write ups.

Winners will receive exciting prizes.

30/08/2019, 14:55 - Anand Kishore: "The principles of true art is not to portray, but to evoke." - Jerzy Kosinski

Hello 2k19 , 
All of us here at Fine Arts Club For Engineering Students (F.A.C.E.S)  congratulate you all for admission in newly batch of 2019. Enough of boring days sitting in class and doodling away at the back of the notebook! 
We now bring to you exciting event for budding artist in you . Get your creative mind running for ONLINE DOODLING EVENT coming up starting today exclusively for first year (Btech ,  Mca , Msc )  NIT jsr students  and first year IIIT students.

Event details are as follows:
You all have to prepare a doodle or pictorial doodle with one of the themes mentioned below :

*Doodle-*
1)how you want to picture the adult version of your childhood's favourite cartoon character
2)a doodle on how you expect /see your college life to be 

*Pictorial doodle-*
1)Spun a story
2)Comical 

*1.Guidelines for Doodling-you can use pen/pencils/colors and  the doodle should be made on A4 size paper.After making you have to click a photo of it and message us on our facebook page along with your name , branch , topic and roll number.*
 *2.Guidelines for pictorial doodling -  You have to click a picture and doodle on it. While doodling with any editor , you can only use emojis , standard shapes, text and sketch tool. When done, message the photo on our facebook page along with your id details mentioned above.*


3) Entries will be accepted till --- *8th September midnight* .
4) Top 3 entries will be awarded during the time of inductions i.e - *21st -22nd September*.
5)Try to avoid copying directly from internet. Use your own imagination. Plagiarism will not be entertained.
For more details feel free to contact us.
Anmol - 9801119003
Kamal-7995120400

07/09/2019, 00:13 - +91 93046 15925: "The principles of true art is not to portray, but to evoke." - Jerzy Kosinski

Hello 2k19 , 
All of us here at Fine Arts Club For Engineering Students (F.A.C.E.S)  congratulate you all for admission in newly batch of 2019. Enough of boring days sitting in class and doodling away at the back of the notebook! 
We now bring to you exciting event for budding artist in you . Get your creative mind running for ONLINE DOODLING EVENT coming up starting today exclusively for first year (Btech ,  Mca , Msc )  NIT jsr students  and first year IIIT students.

Event details are as follows:
You all have to prepare a doodle or pictorial doodle with one of the themes mentioned below :

*Doodle-*
1)how you want to picture the adult version of your childhood's favourite cartoon character
2)a doodle on how you expect /see your college life to be 

*Pictorial doodle-*
1)Spun a story
2)Comical 

*1.Guidelines for Doodling-you can use pen/pencils/colors and  the doodle should be made on A4 size paper.After making you have to click a photo of it and message us on our facebook page along with your name , branch , topic and roll number.*
 *2.Guidelines for pictorial doodling -  You have to click a picture and doodle on it. While doodling with any editor , you can only use emojis , standard shapes, text and sketch tool. When done, message the photo on our facebook page along with your id details mentioned above.*


3) Entries will be accepted till --- *8th September midnight* .
4) Top 3 entries will be awarded during the time of inductions i.e - *21st -22nd September*.
5)Try to avoid copying directly from internet. Use your own imagination. Plagiarism will not be entertained.
For more details feel free to contact us.
Anmol - 9801119003
Kamal-7995120400

*Doodle-*
1)how you want to picture the adult version of your childhood's favourite cartoon character

*Pictorial doodle-*
1)Spun a story
2)Comical

22/09/2019, 00:22 - +91 93046 15925: *"Art enables us to find ourselves and lose ourselves at the same time."* 

Do you ever feel that serenity once you express your feelings through your art?? If you ever did, then you know what it takes to express yourself and to enhance the calmness inside you!!
Guess what we have in store for you? *Well , it's the  oldest and the largest club of NIT Jamshedpur , F.A.C.E.S. (Fine Arts Club for Engineering Students)*. 

We are here with a two day art fiesta , searching for creative engineers with artistic skills , extraordinary thinking ability and capabilities of bringing ideas into reality.

*INDUCTIONS 2019*

Dates - *22nd and 23rd sept'19*
Venue - *312 & 322 (civil department)*
Timing - *5 pm onwards*

In the 2 day Art fiesta we will be having 3 types of competitions followed by a personal interview round.

#Day_1 , *Event 1 : ONE AMONG THREE*
Type- solo event 
Sketching , painting and collage making are the breath of art. In this you will be given to choose between these three. Topics and materials will be provided on spot. And you will have to prepare either a painting or a sketch or a collage  in given span of time.

#Day_1 , *Event 2 : LIVE CANVAS*
Type- group event (team of two )

The most enjoyable event is of live canvas. In this event you have to smear on your partners face or hand on the basis of theme provided.
All those who dream of transforming into butterflies , ghosts , witches , animals...FACES is providing you the perfect stage for the same. Pls note the colors provided will be nontoxic , non skin affecting and one wash removable paints.

#Day_2 , *Event 1 : JUNK ARTS*
Type - group event ( team of two)
This is a mega event of art fiesta
As the name suggests in this event you and your partner will have to make an artistic 2D , 3D model , something attractive , beautiful and thoughtful out of the set of junks.

#Day_2, *Event 2 : PERSONAL INTERVIEW*

Here ur interest &skills will be judged by a panel of judges. This event may start on the first day itself i.e carrying it sideways along with the other events. So everyone is requested to carry your previous art and craft work snapshots as all this will add credits in your selection criteria.

Please note :- 

# During the 2 day event we will be providing you all the necessary materials you don't have to bring anything.

# The topics will be provided on spot.

# For team events you need to arrange a partner. If you are unable to do so pls let us know we will do it for you at the time of the event.

# There will be a good number of fun events too and no need to mention many exciting prizes are there to be grabbed.

*Believe us, you got the right skills and it's time to test it now and we will make sure you are going to have fun and no one's returning without some beautiful memories!*


Also find the *FACES TEASER* attached with this. 

*See you at Inductions* !!

For any queries related please contact : 
Anmol (+91 9801119003)
Kamal ( +91 7995120400)

23/09/2019, 08:57 - +91 93046 15925: *Team Phocus Inductions* 
Greetings freshers and sophomores!
The fever's here with the carnival of cultural and dramatics society now closing in, let loose your creativity and imagination from behind those camera lenses! 

*Phocus* welcomes those that have always desired to show a different perspective, tell an untold story to the world out there. 
Speculate your imagination and turn it into reality through
• *Photography*
• *Film Making*

*Photography*
All the candidates need to submit a total of 6 photographs on 3 themes out of 5 provided below.
The themes for photography are:
 •Landscape
 •Black and White
 •Architecture
 •Street 
 •Independent
*P.S. try to provide caption against each photograph*

*Film Making*
Make a video on any one of the following themes.
(The entry should not be longer than 2 minutes )
The themes for film making are:
 •Campus tour
 •Travelling
 •Independent 
                     (Or)
Candidate can do *any one* of the following tasks.

*Tasks:*
 1. Narrate a story and send the voice recording
 2. Write a short story on memories of camera.
 3. Write a short review of these short films and rate it on scale of 5. (Links are attached below)
https://youtu.be/nkGuMIs67KI
https://youtu.be/ITM53HpTSr8

*Mail your images(in pdf format) with subject : "Phocus induction 2019 Your_name your_regID"at*
 phocus_nit@nitjsr.ac.in
---------------------------------------------
*video and voice recordings should be mailed (with proper subject indicated as above) at* phocus.nitjamshedpur@gmail.com 
*Last date of submission : 26th Sept 2019 midnight*

29/09/2019, 23:12 - VishalKR_45: <Media omitted>
29/09/2019, 23:12 - VishalKR_45: Greetings Freshers!
To introduce you to the quizzing culture of our college and give you a taste of the competition before the Grand Quizzing Week (GQW),
QuNITe, The Official Quizzing Club of NIT Jamshedpur presents before you Pre-GQW, an online quizzing event.
*The Rules of Pre-GQW are as follows:*
1). Pre-GQW is exclusively for the first year students (BTech, MTech, MCA and MSc) of NIT Jamshedpur and IIIT Ranchi. 
2). From 30th September, every night two questions will be posted on the QuNITe Facebook group for 7 days i.e till 6th October at 10 p.m. & 10:30 p.m sharp.
3.)One participant  can answer a question only once. No editing, deleting or recommenting will be allowed thereafter.
4). Fastest finger first, i.e only first 3 correct answers (answered in proper pattern) will be considered as winners for the day. *But don't forget to post your answers even if you are late, we are gonna select a lucky winner every day irrespective of the time when he/she posts the answer. Once we get the list of all lucky winners(1 per question), we will again pick 5 out of them and will reward them as well.*
5.)30 mins duration will be given for each question and answers within this period will only be considered.
6.) *Most Important, the format for answering the question(in the comment section only)will be -*
*YOUR ANSWER <SPACE>#GQW*
Please follow the above-mentioned pattern as answers in this format will only be considered. *No editing is allowed.*
7). The first three correct answers will be considered and 10, 7 and 5 points respectively will be awarded in the order in which they appear first.
8). Correct answer and winners, lucky winners will be announced the next day in the morning.
9). The final results will be declared on 8th October. The top three positions and the lucky winners will be given prizes during the GQW. In case of ties, the one with more scores of the higher value shall be adjudged ahead of other.
Join the QuNITe group on Facebook (link provided below) for more nuances:
https://m.facebook.com/groups/116899075045197?group_view_referrer=profile_browser
Cash prizes to be won!

If you have any doubts regarding any of the above mentioned rules, feel free to ask!!
Aditya: 9430000276
Vishal: 9304191836
Hope to see you people in the comments section with your lightening fast answers!

✨✨ Meaning of our National Anthem ✨✨
💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎
🇮🇳 Please try to understand the meaning and pronounce it clearly.

Word by word meaning..

🎵Jana            = People
🎵Gana            = Group
🎵Mana           = Mind
🎵Adhinayaka= Leader
🎵Jaya He      = Victory 
🎵Bharata       = India
🎵Bhagya       = Destiny
🎵Vidhata      = Disposer
🎵Punjaba     = Punjab
🎵Sindhu       = Indus
🎵Gujarata    = Gujarat
🎵Maratha    = Marathi Maharashtra
🎵Dravida      = South
🎵Utkala        = Orissa
🎵Banga        = Bengal
🎵Vindhya     =Vindhyas
🎵Himachal   =Himalay
🎵Yamuna     = Yamuna
🎵Ganga        = Ganges
🎵Uchchhala = Moving
🎵Jaladhi      = Ocean
🎵Taranga    = Waves
🎵Tava          = Your
🎵Shubh    =Auspicious
🎵Naame = name
🎵Jage     = Awaken
🎵Tava     = Your
🎵Shubha      = Auspicious
🎵Aashisha = Blessings
🎵Maage     = Ask
🎵Gaahe      = Sing

[  भौतिक राशि Physical quantities अन्य भौतिक राशियों से संबंध* 

1. क्षेत्रफल Area लंबाई × चौड़ाई

2. आयतन Volume लंबाई× चौड़ाई×ऊंचाई

3. द्रव्यमान घनत्व Density द्रव्यमान/आय
4. आवृत्ति Frequency 1/आवर्तकाल

5. वेग Velocity विस्थापन/समय

6. चाल Speed दूरी/समय

7. त्वरण Acceleration वेग/समय

8. बल Force द्रव्यमान × त्वरण

9. आवेग Impulse बल × समय

10. कार्य Work बल × दूरी

11. ऊर्जा Energy बल × दूरी

12. शक्ति Power कार्य/समय

13. संवेग Momentum द्रव्यमान × वेग

14. दाब Pressure बल/क्षेत्रफल

15. प्रतिबल Stress बल/क्षेत्रफल

16. विकृति Strain विमा में परिवर्तन/मूल विमा

17. प्रत्यास्थता गुणांक Coefficient of elasticity प्रतिबल/विकृति

18. पृष्ठ तनाव Surface tension बल/लंबाई

19. पृष्ठ ऊर्जा Surface energy ऊर्जा/क्षेत्रफल

20. वेग प्रवणता Velocity gradient वेग/दूरी

21. दाब प्रवणता Pressure gradient दाब/दूरी

22. श्यानता गुणांक Coefficient of viscosity बल/(क्षेत्रफल× वेग प्रवणता)

23. कोण Angel चाप/त्रिज्या

24. त्रिकोणमितीय अनुपात Trigonometric ratio लंबाई/लंबाई

25. कोणीय वेग Angular velocity कोण/समय

26. कोणीय त्वरण Angular acelleration कोणीय वेग/समय

27. कोणीय संवेग Angular momentum जड़त्व आघूर्ण × कोणीय वेग

28. जड़त्व आघूर्ण Moment of inertia द्रव्यमान× (परिभ्रमण त्रिज्या)2

29. बल आघूर्ण Torque बल × दूरी

30. कोणीय आवृत्ति Angular frequency 2π × आवृत्ति

31. गुरुत्वीय सार्वत्रिक नियतांक Universal constant of gravity बल× (दूरी)2/(द्रव्यमान)2

32. प्लांक नियतांक Plank’s constant ऊर्जा/आवृत्ति

33. विशिष्ट उष्मा Specific heat उष्मीय ऊर्जा/(द्रव्यमान× ताप)

34. उष्मा धारिता Heat capacity ऊष्मीय ऊर्जा/ताप

35. बोल्टजमान नियतांक Boltzmann’s constant ऊर्जा/ताप

36. स्टीफन नियतांक Stefan’s constant (ऊर्जा/क्षेत्रफल× समय)/(ताप)4

37. गैस नियतांक Gas constant (दाब× आयतन)/(मोल× ताप )

38. आवेश Charge विद्युत धारा × समय

39. विभवातंर Potential difference कार्य/आवेश

40. प्रतिरोध Resistance विभवांतर/विद्युत धारा

41. धारिता Capacity आवेश/विभवांतर

42. विद्युत क्षेत्र Electric field वैद्युत बल/आवेश

43. चुम्बकीय क्षेत्र Magnetic field बल/(विद्युत धारा× लंबाई)

44. चुम्बकीय फ्लक्स Magnetic flux चुम्बकीय क्षेत्र × लंबाई

45. प्रेरकत्व Inductance चुम्बकीय फ्लक्स/विद्युत धारा

46. वीन नियतांक Wein’s constant तरंगदैर्ध्य ×ताप

47. चालकता Conductivity 1/प्रतिरोध

48. एंट्रॅापी Entropy ऊष्मीय ऊर्जा / ताप

49. गुप्त उष्मा Latent heat उष्मीय ऊर्जा / द्रव्यमान

50. तापीय प्रसार गुणांक Coefficient of thermal expansion विमा में परिवर्तन / (मूल विमा × ताप )

nbsp51. आयतन प्रत्यास्थता गुणांक Bulk modulus ( आयतन × दाब में परिवर्तन )/आयतन में परिवर्तन

52. वैद्युत प्रतिरोधकता Electric resistance ( प्रतिरोध × क्षेत्रफल )/ लंबाई

53. वैद्युत द्विध्रुव आघूर्ण Electric dipole moment बल आघूर्ण / विद्युत क्षेत्र

54. चुम्बकीय द्विध्रुव आघूर्ण Magnetic dipole moment बल आघूर्ण / चुम्बकीय क्षेत्र

55. चुम्बकीय क्षेत्र प्रबलता चुम्बकीय आघूर्ण / आयतन

56. अपवर्तनांक Refractive index निर्वात में प्रकाश की चाल/माध्यम में प्रकाश की चाल

57. तरंग संख्या Wave number 2π / तरंगदैर्ध्य

58. विकिरण शक्ति Radiant power उत्सर्जित ऊर्जा / समय

59. विकिरण तीव्रता Radiant intensity विकिरण शक्ति / घन कोण

60. हबल नियतांक Hubble constant पश्च सरण चाल /दूरी
[09/10, 10:54 pm] Rameshwar Prajapati: जीव विज्ञान के प्रश्न- 
1.: - मांसपेशियों में किस अम्ल के एकत्रित होने से थकावट आती है?
Ans : - लैक्टिक अम्ल
2.: - अंगूर में कौन-सा अम्ल पाया जाता है?
Ans : - टार्टरिक अम्ल

Ans : - -ऑरगेनोलॉजी

Ans : - तंत्रिका कोशिका
5.: - दाँत मुख्य रूप से किस पदार्थ के बने होते हैं?
Ans : - डेंटाइन के
6.: - किस जंतु की आकृति पैर की चप्पल के समान होती है?
Ans : - पैरामीशियम
7.: - केंचुए की कितनी आँखें होती हैं?
Ans : - एक भी नहीं
8.: - गाजर किस विटामिन का समृद्ध स्रोत है?
Ans : - विटामिन A
9.: - निम्न में से किस पदार्थ में प्रोटीन नहीं पाया जाता है?
Ans : - चावल
10.: - मानव का मस्तिष्क लगभग कितने ग्राम का होता है?
Ans : - 1350
11.: - रक्त में पायी जाने वाली धातु है
Ans : - -लोहा
12.: - किण्वन का उदाहरण है
Ans : - -दूध का खट्टा होना,खाने की ब्रेड का बनना,गीले आटे का खट्टा होना
13.: - निम्न में से कौन-सा आहार मानव शरीर में नये ऊतकों की वृद्धि के लिए पोषक तत्व प्रदान करता है?
Ans : - पनीर
14.: - निम्न में से कौन एक उड़ने वाली छिपकली है?
Ans : - ड्रेको
15.: - घोंसला बनाने वाला एकमात्र साँप कौन-सा है?
Ans : - किंग कोबरा
16.: - भारत में पायी जाने वाली सबसे बड़ी मछली कौन-सी है?
Ans : - ह्वेल शार्क
17.: - दालें किसका एक अच्छा स्रोत होती हैं?
Ans : - प्रोटीन
18.: - देशी घी में से सुगन्ध क्यों आती है?
Ans : - डाइएसिटिल के कारण
19.: - इन्द्रधनुष में किस रंग का विक्षेपण अधिक होता है?
Ans : - लाल रंग
20.: - टेलीविजन का आविष्कार किसने किया था?
Ans : - जे. एल. बेयर्ड
21: - हीरा चमकदार क्यों दिखाई देता है?
Ans : - सामूहिक आंतरिक परावर्तन के कारण
22.: - ‘गोबर गैस’ में मुख्य रूप से क्या पाया जाता है।
Ans : - मिथेन
23.: - दूध की शुद्धता का मापन किस यन्त्र से किया जाता है?
Ans : - लैक्टोमीटर
24.: - पृथ्वी पर सबसे अधिक मात्रा में पाया जाने वाला धातु तत्त्व कौन-सा है?
Ans : - ऐलुमिनियम
25.: - मोती मुख्य रूप से किस पदार्थ का बना होता है?

27.: - किस प्रकार के ऊतक शरीर के सुरक्षा कवच का कार्य करते हैं?

28.: - मनुष्य ने सर्वप्रथम किस जन्तु को अपना पालतू बनाया?

29.: - किस वैज्ञानिक ने सर्वप्रथम बर्फ़ के दो टुकड़ों को आपस में घिसकर पिघला दिया?

30.: - सबसे अधिक तीव्रता की ध्वनि कौन उत्पन्न करता है?

Ans : - -जड़ों से
40.: - ‘विटामिन-सी’ का सबसे अच्छा स्त्रोत क्या है?
Ans : - आंवला
  ☄भारतीय संविधान - प्रश्नोत्तर☄


प्रश्‍न 1- भारतीय संविधान सभा की प्रथम बैठक कब हुई । 
उत्‍तर - 9 दिसम्‍बर 1946 । 
प्रश्‍न 2- स‍ंविधान सभा का स्‍थाई अध्‍यक्ष कौन था । 
उत्‍तर - डॉ. राजेंन्‍द्र प्रसाद । 
प्रश्‍न 3- संविधान सभा का अस्‍थाई अध्‍यक्ष कौन था । 
उत्‍तर - डॉ. सच्चिदानंद सिन्‍हा । 
प्रश्‍न 4- संविधान सभा की प्रारूप समिति के अध्‍यक्ष कौन थे । 
उत्‍तर - डॉ. भीमराव अम्‍बेडकर । 
प्रश्‍न 5- संविधान सभा का औपचारिक रूप से प्रतिपादन किसने किया । 
उत्‍तर - एम. एन. राय । 
प्रश्‍न 6- भारत में संविधान सभा गठित करने का आधार क्‍या था । 
उत्‍तर - कैबिनेट मिशन योजना (1946) । 
प्रश्‍न 7- संविधान के गठन की मांग सर्वप्रथम 1895 में किस व्‍यक्ति ने की । 
उत्‍तर - बाल गंगाधर तिलक । 
प्रश्‍न 8- संविधान सभा में देशी रियासतों के कितने प्रतिनिधि थे । 
उत्‍तर - 70 । 
प्रश्‍न 9- संविधान सभा में किस देशी रियासत के प्रतिनिधि ने भाग नही लिया । 
उत्‍तर - हैदराबाद । 
प्रश्‍न 10- बी. आर. अम्‍बेडकर कहॉं के संविधान सभा में निर्वाचित हुए । 
उत्‍तर - बंगाल से । 
प्रश्‍न 11- संविधान सभा का संवैधानिक सलाहकार किसे नियुक्‍त किया गया था । 
उत्‍तर - बी. एन. राव । 
प्रश्‍न 12- संविधान सभा की प्रारूप समिति का गठन कब हुआ । 
उत्‍तर - 29 अगस्‍त 1947 । 
प्रश्‍न 13- संविधान की प्रारूप समिति के समक्ष प्रस्‍तावना का प्रस्‍ताव किसने रखा । 
उत्‍तर - जवाहर लाल नेहरू । 
प्रश्‍न 14- संविधान सभा की रचना हेतु संविधान का विचार सर्वप्रथम किसने प्रस्‍तुत किया । 
उत्‍तर - स्‍वराज पार्टी ने 1924 में । 
प्रश्‍न 15- संविधान सभा में भारत के संविधान को कब स्‍वीकृत किया । 
उत्‍तर - 26 नवम्‍बर 1946 । 
प्रश्‍न 16- संविधान को बनाने में कितना समय लगा । 
उत्‍तर - 2 वर्ष 11 माह 18 दिन । 
प्रश्‍न 17- स‍ंविधान में कितने अनुच्‍छेद है। 
उत्‍तर - 444 । 
प्रश्‍न 18- संविधान में कितने अध्‍याय है।
उत्‍तर - 22 । 
प्रश्‍न 19- भारतीय सभा में कितनी अनुसूचियॉ है। 
उत्‍तर - 12 । 
प्रश्‍न 20- संविधान सभा का चुनाव किस आधार पर हुआ । 
उत्‍तर - वर्गीय मताधिकार पर ।

20/10/2019, 09:17 - +91 73259 62631: *"Acting is not about being someone different. It's finding the similarity in what is apparently different, then finding myself in there."*
                            *-Meryl Streep*

Everyday is a new challenge in this competitive world. The society is just too obnoxious to spare you a breath. Situations are ready to tear you apart. This fills your heart with inexplicable feelings which are left unexpressed. At these times you need to throw them out but don't get a way to do so.
So it's time  to act out your unsaid emotions. 

*Team Aahwan* the official dramatics club of NIT JAMSHEDPUR is holding its induction.
*Date:-21st and 22nd October*
*Time:-5pm to 9pm*
*Vanue-Vsg*

*Team Aahwan* is the name for expression for not only those who act but to each and every one who has some unsaid things left behind. So *team aahwan* requests all the first year students to show their enthusiasm via their participation in huge numbers.
So let the expressions flow out and sieze the day.

*For any query contact*
*Kunal - 9110161408*
*Mayank- 91101 92391*

Beholding opportunities to show your creativity and skills, Vidhaan brings to you it's *model-making and paper presentation event, Nirmaan*, where you can use all your creativity and presence of mind and come up with any unique topic which relates to civil engineering. 

• You have to participate in teams of 3.
• You can choose any topic provided it relates to civil engineering. 
• You have to make a working/ non-working 3-d model for your chosen topic and also prepare a PowerPoint presentation about the same. 
• Your presentation should focus on the working and mechanism of your model and should definitely explain the advantages and disadvantages of your proposed idea. 
• There is a limit to the time each team gets to explain the idea and the time limit is of 10 minutes exceeding which there will be negative points given to the team.


As the first step of participating in the event, you need to send the abstract of your topic on koursimrances@gmail.com   between *28th October* and *3rd November*.
The abstract should contain the following details:
• Team name
• Name of the team leader
• Name of the team members and their contact details 
• Your topic
• A brief description of your idea. (In about 4 to 6 lines)

Nirmaan will be held on *10th of November at 8:30 AM*. And the participants will be judged on the basis of the creativity and uniqueness of their idea and on  their presentation by our esteemed panel. 

So, put your brains to work and come up with something which indeed is unique. 
And remember,
Create, Enhance, and Sustain.

Nishant - 8709702154

01/11/2019, 17:52 - Ayush Jaiswal NIT/CIVIL: *Hello juniors*
A job interview is not a test to your knowledge but your ability to use it at the right time.
Well, you are called for the interview because you have the necessary skills to fit in the job. But, are you prepared? Do you understand the interview process and it's context? And most importantly, do you realise that it is competitive? 
If the answer is a No, you still have time to get ready for it. 

Interview is undoubtedly the most important process in staff selection and being a two way interaction, it holds prime significance for any student.
Acknowledging the importance of the interview ŕound in a student's life and understanding the confusion and nervousness a candidate goes through, Vidhaan come up with it's event, *Roobaroo*.

Roobaroo is going to be a PI session where the participants will get to experience a Personal Interview which surely will be beneficial for all who show up for the event. 

Roobaroo will be held on *10th of November 2019 in Room no. 312 and 322* of the civil Department. 
The time slots of the event are as follows:
*Slot 1- 9:45 AM*
*Slot 2- 1:00 PM*

*It is mandatory for all the participants to bring a printed CV with themselves for the PI.* (No hand-written CV allowed)

So, don't miss the opportunity to experience an interview session and check your abilities of using  your knowledge and skills at the right time. 

For further queries, contact :
Rohit Kumar - 7992238518
Rashmi Rathee -7909035267

25/12/2019, 11:53 - Priyanshu NIT/CIVIL: One year back, one year forth, few years back, few years ahead your special day i.e. your birthday maybe a day on which a  great personality took birth or could even be possibly a day which witnessed an event that became a  history!
It's pretty sure that all must have wondered about it or googled it some time or the other. On finding anything great you must have found yourself inexplicably overwhelmed.

Suppose your birthday is on the 22nd of July and after the launch of Chandryaan-2 on this very day, your supposed statement would be "Arey yaar mere birthday ke din hi Chandrayaan-2 launch hua tha !!!!" and that too full of exuberance.

Well well this is an informal way of putting something exciting, here OJASS presents before you Online Event-2  *BIRTH-DATE-DEETS* where you just need to showcase your this expression through words.
You just need to write your birthday along which you also need to mention that great thing which happened on your birthday!

*What to post?*
1. You can post about any famous personality whom you share your birthday with.
2. Any event which is historic in the field of science may be posted too.

*Where and with what specifications to post about ?*
1. Post it on your Facebook Timeline.
2. Include #my_birthday #birth_date_deets #OJASS20 in your post.
3. You can even nominate your friends to participate in the event by tagging them.
4. It is mandatory that your post security is public.

*How will the winner be decided ?*
1. 1 point will be rewarded for each Like, 
     2 points for each Reaction, 
     3 points for each Share.
2. There will be a bonus of 20 points on posting anything related to science.
3.  Extra 20 points will be for creative presentation which may include pictures or description of your content.

The winner will be awarded with exciting goodies.

Note:
1. This event is open for all the batches.
2. The deadline for the entries is 11:59 pm, 3rd January 2020 and no entries after this shall be considered viable for winning.
3. MENTION YOUR BIRTHDAY AND THEN WRITE ABOUT THE GREAT THING. (Check the comments section for the sample.) 
4. The post should be in correct format for further evaluation. The decision of the OJASS Team regarding the winners and/or any other discrepancy will be considered final.

So go on and Google your birthday!

21/03/2020, 18:20 - Royal Rajput: सार्वजनिक अपील:-

१. थेथरई न करें। घर में चुपेचाप बैठिये। थेथर लोग के लिए सरकार अलग से टास्क फ़ोर्स तैयार कर देगी तब ले लोटा बउआते रहिएगा।

२. लबर-लबर करके सामान नहीं ख़रीदिए। दुकान भागल नहीं जा रहा है।

३. बढ़िया से हाथ पैर धोके बिस्तर में नुकाये रहिए।

४. मन नहीं लगे त घर के भीतरे से जोगिरा गाके सब लोगिन को मनोरंजन कराते रहिए।
उससे का है कि मनोबल बना रहता है

५. बिना मतलब का दवाई लिखवाने हॉस्पिटल जाने का कौनो ज़रूरत नहीं है।

६. घर के छोटका बाल बूतरू और बूढ़ पुरनिया सब को घरे में हाथ गोर बाँध दीजिए।

७. भोरे खरिहान जाना है त अकेले जाइए।

८. दोस्त यार संगे पंघत खाने कौनो नहीं जाएगा।

९. बाक़ी टेन्शन का कोई बात नहीं है। कुछ दिन अकेले खैनी रगड़िए अकेले खाइए।

१०. कोरोना झड़वाने भगता के पास नहीं जाइए; भगत जी अपना कोरोना हॉस्पिटल में झड़वा रहे हैं।

११. घरे में से भगवान जी को गोर लाग लीजिए ।

बाक़ी अप्डेट करते रहेंगे। बने रहिए।

16/04/2020, 11:21 - Shubham Roger NIT/CIVIL: *विजय शंख* 

मंजर खौफनाक तो है पर ढूंढो तो सुकून मिल जाएगा 
सिर्फ बहता हुआ खून नहीं रगों में जुनून मिल जाएगा 
जुनूनी वो जो औरों में जान भरने की कोशिश कर रहा है 
और इस दुविधा में अपनी जान को ताखे पर धर रहा है
इस अदृश्य युद्ध में कितने चिकित्सक हुए शहीद है 
विजय शंख शिघ्र बजेगा इसकी पूरी उम्मीद है 

करना ही हमको क्या है बस घर में दिन बिताना है
रिश्तो में प्रेम बढ़ाने का यही तो उचित बहाना है 
कुछ बातें करो कुछ खत लिखो कुछ फोन करो 
फिर भी मन नहीं लगता तो कसरत और अनुलोम-विलोम करो 
इस भारी विपत्ति से बचना है तो इतनी सी बात समझना है  
स्वास्थ्य संस्थाओं की बातों का कथन स्वरूप पालन करना है
आज देश का नीति देख दुश्मन भी मुरीद है 
विजय शंख शिघ्र बजेगा इसकी पूरी उम्मीद है

कहीं लोग अकेले हैं तो कहीं खाने के लाले हैं 
मातृभूमि को यह न लगे हम इन बच्चों को क्यों पाले हैं 
अगर सामर्थ्य हो तो आओ और भाल कृपाल उठाओ 
छोड़ो यह सब तुम बस गरीबों में खाना बटवाओ 
सब साथ में है खड़े क्या अमीर क्या गरीब है 
तभी तो विजय शंख बजने का इतना अधिक उम्मीद है

         — _शुभम् कुमार_

28/04/2020, 08:01 - Shubham Roger NIT/CIVIL: *It's big but please read. It's about our future!* 

After getting some good suggestions regarding my yesterday's appeal, I have come up with a better plan.

Lockdown for one or few days is like adding few drops of water in container on a particular day while we keep removing a mug of water from it every day! It will just shift the doom's day to a few days later not by years! 


So, to nurture our mother earth, we have to think in some depth and solid way. And that leads me to the point how the destruction started! *"Just reverse it or stop it and we will make our mother very healthy and wealthy once again!"* *Then feeding from that mother we will become such too.* 

Why to wait for govt. to take any such decision! Aren't we so much capable to care our mother!
Also the reality is govt. is mainly run by morons and industrialists and they will never keep environment prior to development and their profits. They will only focus on development either it is sustainable or not! That's why even after spending so much funds on Ganga and other gifts of nature, the result is zero. 

*People go to buy even vegetables in their luxury vehicles! Everyone wants to use their private vehicle instead of public, whether necessary or not! A teenage who is not even 18 force their parents to buy personal vehicle just for wandering( they are also one of the main part of accidents).*
*Can't we keep our vehicles pollution checked! Can't we install solar panels instead of inverters if it fits in our budget! And biggest of all, Can't we stop burning crackers! The beauty of India which illuminate by diyas and candle, get hide in the dust and dirt of crackers. Whenever you go to burn crackers next time, remember you are burning a part of your mother's body.* 

And I am sure these will be enough to cure our future as well as earth. According to WHO, around 40 lakhs people die worldwide only due to diseases casued by PM 2.5(Particulate Matter), which is just one part of pollution among so many. There are many such true but harsh datas. You can search it. It's more destructive than any virus like a slow poison! It has been already too late but atleast we can start now to fulfill our duty to the environment and next generation.

Handling rest things like factories, resources, etc., I leave on govt. It's in their power to regulate it sustainably. But we should start from our side. If still not, then get ready to face even worse situation than present. There is a very well known dialogue:- " *Bhagwan k bharose mat baithiye, ho skta h wo apke bharose baitha ho* ".

Share this message if you are ready to prove yourself a liable child of mother earth.

 — A Responsible Citizen.

05/06/2020, 20:25 - Anand Kishore: Hello everyone, I hope you all are healthy and safe. I also assume that you have prepared for the examination too. So, all it remains now is: How to take exam?

*A Step to Step Guide to crack the exam*

*_1st 15mins_*

Everyone is required to solve their papers till the 1st quarter of an hour; u may take help of your notes or Google. 

After this, take a page and *write the question code* and *_write the answer in text(mtlb pura answer likhna hai, naa ki a, b,c,d!)_* Take a snap of this page and upload it on Mission 2020. 

*_Remaining 15 to 30 min_*

Keep on solving other remaining questions. During this time and keep on uploading the answers in missing 2020 grp in every 5 to 7 min(example _ Agar next 5 min me koe 3 question solve krta hai toh usko ek sath paper me likh kr upload kr de and isko 30 min tk continues rakhen), if the _tally people_ feel that some questions have low frequency of answers; then they will ask for more responses(answers) on Mission 2020 PRO. 

*_ 🛑🛑🛑 _* 
Everytime cross check your answers before uploading and make sure that you have not posted any wrong answer on the "Mission 2020 Group".

After final cross checking of answers  by the moderation team of _PRO_ group, you will have the access to the final tallied answers in MISSION 2020 PRO grp.


🔥🔥🔥
*NOTE- DO NOT POST ANSWERS TO ANY QUESTION ON WHICH YOU HAVE DOUBT*🔥🔥🔥
untill asked by the moderation/tally team.


And everyone is requested to slove the questions as much as they can with much confidence and surety of getting right answers.


*Please do not depend on others completely*.

मार्च में कोरोना देश में था, राज्य में नहीं था।
अप्रैल में कोरोना राज्य में था, जिला में नहीं था।
मई में कोरोना जिला में था, शहर में नहीं था।
जून में कोरोना शहर में था, मोहल्ले में नहीं था।
जुलाई में कोरोना मोहल्ले में था, घर में नहीं था।
अगस्त में कोरोना आपके घर पर दस्तक दे सकता है।
सबसे ज्यादा बचने और सुरक्षित रहने का समय अब है।

So if u can support please make a small contribution from ur side as his father was earning a salary lesser than expected and is having 4 children to educate. He  has to undergo 24 chemotherapy which costs more than 50k per month with medicines.Our small support can save the lives of many. Thank you.

4. प्रतियोगिता से जुड़े बाकी सभी निर्देश कल दिए जाएगे l

 *Drawing /Painting Competition* 
1. Painting /Drawing competition will be held tomorrow 26th September 2020 at 4pm sharp. All the students who wish to participate need to fill this form (Compulsory) - 
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScdoqDq7iI7_YDWxSuijkfIzMDEM5vKSnr9lQADoXLFrW5e0g/viewform?usp=sf_link
2. The topic of your art shall be disclosed on spot after which you will have to make a picture related to the given topic within a certain time frame (adequate time will be given). 
3. Winner takes home a 1000 rupee cash prize while the runner up will get a cash prize of 500 rupees. All the participants will be given participation certificates. 
4. Rest of the instructions will be given tomorrow. 
Note - The result of all the competitions will be passed on to you at the end of this pakhwada.
 *Form closes tomorrow at 12 PM.*

To quench your thirst for technical and industrial knowledge, we bring to you one of the stalwarts of Indian Mining Industry to share his experience with us. We are honored to have Former Executive Director of UCIL and recipient of *National Geoscience Award-2013* for Sustainable Mineral Development, *Dr. Akshay Kumar Sarangi Sir* as our guest speaker this week.

His 37 years of extensive and dynamic career in the field of mining and geology is studded with all kinds of laurels. Dr. Sarangi’s work in empowering sustainable mining and capacity building in Nuclear Power has been widely recognized in industrial and academic circles. He is a renowned technocrat, scientist and expert on Uranium geology and mining. Having worked under pioneers of Indian Nuclear Programme like  Dr. R. Chidambaram and Dr. A. Kakodkar, his experience is an invaluable asset for any ambitious upcoming engineers and researchers. Dr. Sarangi Sir will be guiding us on *“Geology for beginners in Civil Engineering”*

The guest lecture is being organized on Google Meet platform on *27th October 2020 at 5:30pm*

All those interested are required to fill this google form : https://forms.gle/UryNSWaaFFX55i348

You are requested to start joining from 5:15pm through the following link: https://meet.google.com/kei-zonq-gqi
